Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Sheffield. 
    See also Table 2, note (b).

That part which until 1.4.1933 formed part of the parish of 
    Norton. Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of Eckington. See 
    also Table 2, note (a).

Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Sheffield. 
    See also Table 2, note (b).

Created 1.4.1904 from the parishes of Ecclesall Bierlow, Nether 
    Hallam, Norton WIthin, Heeley and Upper Hallam. Abolished 1.4.1933 and added to the parish of Sheffield. See also Table 2, note (b).
Abolished 1.4.1904 and added to the parish of Ecclesall.

Created 23.12.1880 out of the parish of Nether Hallam. Abolished 
    1.4.1904 and added to the parish of Ecclesall.

That part which until 1.4.1934 formed part of the parish of 
    Totley. See also Table 2, note (b).
Abolished 1.4.1904 and added to the parish of Ecclesall.

Abolished 1.4.1933 and divided between the parishes of Sheffield 
    and Coal Aston. See also Table 2, notes (a) and (b).

Created 31.10.1901 out of the parishes of Norton and Beauchief. 
    Abolished 1.4.1904 and added to the parish of Ecclesall.

That part which until 1.4.1934 formed the parishes of 
    Beauchief, Dore and Ecclesall and parts of the parishes of Norton and 
    Totley. See also Table 2, note (b).

Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Sheffield 
    and Holmesfield. See also Table 2, notes (a) and (b).
Abolished 1.4.1904 and added to the parish of Ecclesall.
